✅ Assumption:

Tables already exist:

Student(Student_ID, …)

Hall(Hall_ID, Hall_Name, other columns…)

Course(Course_ID, Course_Name, other columns…)



---

✅ 1. Remove all columns from Hall except Hall_ID, Hall_Name

You must drop unwanted columns one by one:

ALTER TABLE Hall DROP COLUMN Column1;
ALTER TABLE Hall DROP COLUMN Column2;
ALTER TABLE Hall DROP COLUMN Column3;

(Replace Column1, Column2, etc. with real column names.)


---

✅ 2. Remove all columns from Course except Course_ID, Course_Name

ALTER TABLE Course DROP COLUMN Column1;
ALTER TABLE Course DROP COLUMN Column2;

(Replace with actual column names.)


---

✅ 3. Make Student_ID a Primary Key (if not already)

ALTER TABLE Student
ADD CONSTRAINT PK_Student PRIMARY KEY (Student_ID);


---

✅ 4. Make Course_ID a Primary Key (if not already)

ALTER TABLE Course
ADD CONSTRAINT PK_Course PRIMARY KEY (Course_ID);


---

✅ 5. Make Hall_ID a Primary Key (if not already)

ALTER TABLE Hall
ADD CONSTRAINT PK_Hall PRIMARY KEY (Hall_ID);


---

✅ 6. Add Course_ID and Hall_ID columns to Student table (as foreign keys)

Add the columns:

ALTER TABLE Student
ADD Course_ID INT;

ALTER TABLE Student
ADD Hall_ID INT;

Add foreign key constraints:

ALTER TABLE Student
ADD CONSTRAINT FK_Student_Course
FOREIGN KEY (Course_ID) REFERENCES Course(Course_ID);

ALTER TABLE Student
ADD CONSTRAINT FK_Student_Hall
FOREIGN KEY (Hall_ID) REFERENCES Hall(Hall_ID);


---

✅ 7. Add Hall_Clearance column in Hall Table

ALTER TABLE Hall
ADD Hall_Clearance INT;


---

✅ 8. Set default value of Hall_Clearance to 1

ALTER TABLE Hall
ALTER COLUMN Hall_Clearance SET DEFAULT 1;

(MySQL alternative)

ALTER TABLE Hall
MODIFY Hall_Clearance INT DEFAULT 1;


---

✅ 9. Rename Student Table to Student_Info

ALTER TABLE Student
RENAME TO Student_Info;


---

✅ 10. Rename any column (Example: rename Course_Name → Course_Title)

ALTER TABLE Course
CHANGE COLUMN Course_Name Course_Title VARCHAR(100);


---

✅ 11. Make Composite Primary Keys

Student_Info table (example: Student_ID + Course_ID)

ALTER TABLE Student_Info
ADD CONSTRAINT PK_StudentInfo PRIMARY KEY (Student_ID, Course_ID);

Course table (example: Course_ID + Course_Name)

ALTER TABLE Course
ADD CONSTRAINT PK_Course_Composite PRIMARY KEY (Course_ID, Course_Title);

Hall table (example: Hall_ID + Hall_Name)

ALTER TABLE Hall
ADD CONSTRAINT PK_Hall_Composite PRIMARY KEY (Hall_ID, Hall_Name);


---

✅ 12. Drop Primary Key constraints from all tables

ALTER TABLE Student_Info DROP PRIMARY KEY;
ALTER TABLE Course DROP PRIMARY KEY;
ALTER TABLE Hall DROP PRIMARY KEY;


